<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-34-0499 </DOCNO><TEXT>Digital subtraction angiography (DSA) is now an accepted technique forthe noninvasive evaluation of the cerebral, carotid, abdominal, and peripheralarteries. Until very recently, evaluation of the intrathoracic arterywas suboptimal due to respiratory and cardiac motion. However, advancedtechnical modifications have helped to overcome these hazards to a greatextent. In reviewing the current literature, it becomes evident thatselective application of the digital technique may reduce the numberof patients requiring conventional thoracic angiography.</TEXT></DOC>